  "articleSummary": "This tutorial targets developers and data engineers who need to extract URLs from unstructured text using JavaScript regular expressions. The core thesis advocates a pragmatic two-step workflow: first, employing a permissive, modular regex pattern to cast a wide net for potential URLs, followed by secondary validation to filter invalid matches. The article dissects a concise 120-byte regex into five distinct components—protocol, domain, path, query, and fragment—while clearly distinguishing between extraction and parsing. Maintaining a hands-on, step-by-step tutorial tone, the piece uses recurring metaphors like \"whack-a-mole\" and \"casting a wide net\" to frame the technical breakdown and guide readers from basic pattern recognition to robust implementation.",
